The '''Obbia lark''' ('''''Spizocorys obbiensis''''') is a species of [[lark]] in the family [[Alaudidae]]. It is found in central Somalia, where it is [[Endemism|endemic]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is sub-tropical or tropical dry [[shrubland]].

Formerly or presently, some authorities classified the Obbia lark as belonging to the genus ''[[Calandrella]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://avibase.bsc-eoc.org/species.jsp?avibaseid=D7A55FB3209AAFF7|title=Spizocorys obbiensis - Avibase|website=avibase.bsc-eoc.org|access-date=2016-12-01}}</ref>

